---
name: end-of-day-review
description: End-of-day debrief — Avi reports back on the day's session, fueling, and feel. Compute plan-vs-actual, capture anomalies, queue amendments for tomorrow's morning-check-in. Triggers when Avi says "log today", "wrap the day", "how did I do", "review today", or reports a workout in the evening with end-of-day framing. Distinct from amend-day (which adjusts an active plan mid-day).
when_to_use: Evening of a day where Avi has trained, OR when he explicitly asks to review the day. Don't run this in the morning — that's morning-check-in's job. If a workout was logged today and no end-of-day review exists yet, this is the right Skill.
---

# end-of-day-review

## Step 0 — Load your brain

The Project's Custom Instructions are loaded. Apply voice + ADHD-aware
mode + hard rules.

## Step 1 — Pull today's data

```
GET /api/daily-plans/by-date/{today}
GET /api/workouts?date={today}
GET /api/meals?date={today}
GET /api/nutrition/daily-summary?date={today}
GET /api/health/insights/today
```

## Step 2 — Detect day type

| Signal | Day type |
|--------|----------|
| At least one workout logged | training_day |
| No workout, plan said rest | planned_rest |
| No workout, plan said train | missed_session |
| No workout, no plan | unstructured |

## Step 3 — Compute deltas (only if training_day)

- `effort_delta` = actual_effort − planned_effort
- `duration_delta_pct` = (actual_min − planned_min) / planned_min × 100
- `protein_pct` = actual_protein / target_protein × 100
- `cal_pct` = actual_cal / target_cal × 100
- HR-zone check: easy intent + Z3+ avg HR → flag drift

Anomaly thresholds: |effort_delta| > 2, |duration_delta_pct| > 25%,
protein_pct < 80, cal_pct < 70, HR drift on easy day.

## Step 4 — Generate the review

```
EVENING REVIEW — {today}

WHAT WAS DONE
- {workout type, duration, effort, distance}
- Meals: {N meals, total cal, total protein}
- Subjective: {mood / motivation / soreness if logged}

PLAN vs ACTUAL
- Effort: {actual} vs {planned} ({delta})
- Duration: {actual} vs {planned} ({delta_pct}%)
- Nutrition: {actual_cal}/{target_cal} kcal, {actual_protein}/{target_protein}g protein

ANOMALIES
- {flagged item or "none — execution matched plan"}

INJURY RESPONSE
- {if any active injuries: today's status update}

QUEUED FOR TOMORROW
- {1-3 specific adjustments to surface in tomorrow's morning brief}
```

If day_type was `missed_session`, lead with that and ask what got in
the way; capture answer in `next_steps`.

## Step 5 — Long-session fueling rehearsal nudge

If `duration_minutes` ≥ 60 AND `workout_type IN ('run','hill','hybrid','ruck')`
AND no `fueling_rehearsal` row exists for today's workout: ask
*"Long session today — log the fueling?"* If yes, hand off to
`log-fueling-rehearsal` skill.

## Step 6 — Save the coaching session

```
POST /api/training/coaching
{
  "session_date": "{today}",
  "title": "End-of-day review — {today}",
  "summary": "{the full formatted review above}",
  "key_decisions": [...],
  "adjustments": [...],
  "injury_notes": "{updated status}",
  "nutrition_notes": "{adherence notes}",
  "recovery_notes": "{HRV/sleep observations}",
  "next_steps": "{1-3 concrete things for tomorrow}",
  "ai_source": "claude",
  "tags": ["skill", "end_of_day"]
}
```

## Step 7 — Update today's daily plan

If `today_plan` exists, mark its status: `completed` if anomalies minor,
`partial` if duration < 70%, `missed` if no workout but plan called for
one, `amended` if Avi did a different session than planned.

```
PUT /api/daily-plans/{plan_id}
{
  "status": "...",
  "completion_notes": "{1-2 sentences from review}",
  "actual_exercises": [...if Fitbod-style data captured...]
}
```

## ADHD-aware voice

- Lead with one-line summary of how the day went, then deltas.
- Process win first. *"Five training days this week, no missed sessions
  — hold the streak."* Not "good week!"
- Anomalies stated honestly, no moralizing.
- Queued-for-tomorrow tied to a concrete action.
